# ==============================================================================
# FILE: .gitignore
# PURPOSE: Tells Git which files to NEVER track or commit.
#
# ACADEMIC NOTE — Why .gitignore matters for this project specifically:
#   This project has three categories of sensitive files that must NEVER
#   enter version control:
#     1. SECRETS:  .env contains the Gemini API key. A leaked key can result
#                  in unauthorized API usage and unexpected charges.
#     2. USER DATA: safespace.db contains chat logs. Even though they are
#                  anonymized, committing a research database to a public
#                  repo would be an ethical and potentially legal violation.
#     3. BLOAT:    Python cache files, virtual environments, and OS files
#                  have no place in a repository and inflate its size.
# ==============================================================================

# --- Secrets (CRITICAL) ---
.env
*.env

# --- User Data / Database (CRITICAL) ---
data/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/

# --- Virtual Environments ---
venv/
env/
.venv/
ENV/

# --- SpaCy Models (large, downloaded separately) ---
# These are downloaded via: python -m spacy download en_core_web_lg
*.tar.gz

# --- IDE / Editor ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Logs ---
*.log
logs/

# --- Streamlit ---
.streamlit/secrets.toml
